===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|pen}}, {{m|enm|penne|t=enclosure for animals}}, from {{inh|en|ang|penn|t=enclosure, fold, pen}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*pennō}}, {{m|gem-pro|*pannijō|t=pin, bolt, nail, tack}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bend-|t=pointed peg, nail, edge}}. Related to {{m|en|pin}}.

Sense “prison” originally figurative extension to “enclosure for persons” (1845), later influenced by {{m|en|penitentiary|t=prison}}, being analyzed as an abbreviation (1884).<ref name="oetyld">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

